{{NCAATeamFootballSeason |Year=1962 |Team=Miami Hurricanes |Image= |Conference=Independent |Division= |ShortConference=Independent |CoachRank=18 |APRank=Not ranked |Record=7-4 |ConfRecord=N/A |HeadCoach=[[Andy Gustafson]] |OffCoach= |DefCoach= |OScheme= |DScheme= |StadiumArena=[[Miami Orange Bowl]] |Champion= |BowlTourney=[[Gotham Bowl]] |BowlTourneyResult= L, 34-36 vs. [[Nebraska Cornhuskers football|Nebraska]] }} The '''1962 [[University of Miami]] [[Miami Hurricanes football|Hurricanes]]''' football team's offense scored 189 points while the defense allowed 217 points. The Hurricanes competed in the final [[Gotham Bowl]], held at [[Yankee Stadium (1923)|Yankee Stadium]]. There were just 6,166 people that came to Yankee Stadium for the 1962 game, in which the [[University of Nebraska]] defeated the [[University of Miami]], 36&ndash;34. {{asof|2009}}. the Miami-Nebraska game remains the only college bowl ever played at the stadium.
